## ThetaData v3 endpoint catalog — what works on Options Standard tier

Verified live against the EC2-hosted terminal on 2026-06-02. Update this
if endpoints get added/removed.

### Works (HTTP 200)
  GET /v3/option/list/expirations?symbol=X&format=json
  GET /v3/option/list/strikes?symbol=X&expiration=YYYY-MM-DD&format=json
  GET /v3/option/snapshot/quote?symbol=X&expiration=YYYY-MM-DD&strike=N.NNN&right=C&format=json
  GET /v3/option/snapshot/quote?...&strike=*&right=both    (full chain)
  GET /v3/option/snapshot/trade?...
  GET /v3/option/snapshot/ohlc?...
  GET /v3/option/snapshot/open_interest?...
  GET /v3/option/history/eod?symbol=X&expiration=YYYY-MM-DD&strike=N&right=C&start_date=YYYY-MM-DD&end_date=YYYY-MM-DD&format=json

### NOT available on Standard tier (all returned 404)
  /v3/option/snapshot/implied_volatility
  /v3/option/snapshot/greeks
  /v3/option/snapshot/all
  /v3/option/snapshot/delta
  /v3/option/bulk_snapshot/*
  /v3/option/history/implied_volatility
  /v3/option/historical/*

Implication: IV and greeks must be COMPUTED locally from quote data
(Brenner-Subrahmanyam for ATM IV, full Black-Scholes for non-ATM
greeks). This actually plays well with the data-integrity layer
principle — vendor IV is no longer something we'd have to trust.

### Quirks
  - Strike param is decimal in dollars: 200.00 (not 200000 cents)
  - Date param is ISO YYYY-MM-DD (not 8-digit YYYYMMDD)
  - Default response format is CSV — always pass format=json
  - HTTP 472 = "no data for your request" (e.g. wrong strike for
    expiration). Treat as None, not an error.
  - HTTP 403 = subscription tier insufficient. Log and skip.
  - HTTP 410 = API version mismatch (you used /v2/* paths)
  - Stock endpoints return 403 — we deliberately skipped Stock
    subscription, equity quotes stay on yfinance.

