## P1.2 follow-ups (deferred from 2026-06-02 session)

  1. **Put-call parity check.** Needs spot + risk-free rate + dividend
     yield. We have FRED for rates (DFF). We have yfinance for
     dividends. The check is `|C − P − (S − K·e^(−rT) − q)| <
     tolerance`. Useful but lower priority than staleness — the
     staleness catch already handles the dominant failure mode.

  2. **IV smile monotonicity.** Chain-level check across strikes.
     Catches "this one strike's IV is way off the smile curve" →
     likely vendor cleanup gap. Requires computing IV per strike, which
     fits naturally with the delta-band selection work (P1.4
     follow-up #3).

  3. **Self-regression / intra-tick consistency.** Cache last N IV
     reads per strike, flag when current IV differs by > N standard
     deviations. Most useful intraday during high-volume sessions.
     Deferred — needs in-process state design and tuning.

  4. **Provider-fallback observability.** When sanity rejects
     ThetaData and we fall back to yfinance, that's currently a single
     WARNING log line. Could be surfaced on the observability page as
     a rolling count, with per-flag breakdown. Operator should see
     "sanity rejected 12 quotes today, 9 stale, 3 wide-spread."

