## Project-specific Python conventions seen this session

  - Module-level `_CACHE: Dict[str, tuple] = {}` with TTL from
    TUNABLES — the canonical pattern for cheap in-process caches.
  - `from __future__ import annotations` at top of every file.
  - Logger via `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`.
  - Provider-chain pattern: ordered list of (name, fn) tuples; first
    non-None wins; each fn returns same dict shape or None on failure.
  - Tests in `tests/unit/test_*.py`, mock external deps via
    `monkeypatch.setattr`, never hit real network.
  - Config tunables live in `backend.config.TUNABLES` (dataclass-ish);
    env vars override TUNABLES when both are set.
